net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component

Class ComponentImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.ComponentImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<Component>, net.proteusframework.core.locale.LocaleContextSource, Component
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractButton, Calendar, ComboBox, Container, Field, FileField, ImageComponent, Label, ListComponent, Media, Pager, RichList, Separator, Table, Tabs, Tree

    public abstract class ComponentImpl
extends Object
implements Component
    Base class for all user interface objects. The Component class provides the basic fields and methods needed to handle a user interface component.
    Author:
    Pat B. Double (double@i2rd.com)

      • init

        public void init()
        Description copied from interface: Component

        Called when a Component is first attached to a WindowManager. This means the Component should have valid return values from getApplication(), getLocaleContext(), getParent(). It is preferable to have all construction of the Component go here since a valid LocaleContext, Application object, etc., are available.

        When overriding this method, be sure to call the super class init(). init() is called only once for each Component. The parent component will have been init()ed before init() is called.

      • stateRequested

        public void stateRequested(Map<String,String> state)
        Description copied from interface: Component

        Called to request the component to setup a given state. The state is given by a map of String to String. This method is normally called in response to an application state event to give the component an opportunity to handle itself. This method will call the method of the same name in any child components.

        When overriding this method it is important to call this method (i.e. super.stateRequested(state)) after handling the request. If components are created or removed in this method then the child components to be considered should be after this behavior, therefore calling super.stateRequested(state) last.

        NOTE: Do NOT modify the state map. It is used by other components in the tree and modifying it may produce undesirable behavior.

        Specified by:
        stateRequested in interface Component
        Parameters:
        state - The state map.

      • validate

        public void validate()
        Description copied from interface: Component

        Normally called by the medium to make sure the component is in a valid state before updating the medium. Other classes may safely call as needed. Note however that validating may take a substantial amount of work depending on the subclass implementation!.

        NOTE: When overriding this method, be sure to call the super class validate() as the last statement in the overridden method.

        Specified by:
        validate in interface Component
